        <prj:TechnicalJustification>
            <prj:justificationText>Required sensitivity:

Our recent CSO observations imply a continuum flux density of 100 mJy at the redshifted frequency (346.4 GHz) of the HF J=1-0 transition.  In order to confirm unequivocally our previous detection of HF, we require a signal-to-noise ratio on the continuum of 100 in a 5 km/s channel, corresponding to a sensitivity of 1 mJy in a 5 km/s channel and a total estimated time of 2.33 h. 

Correlator setup:

 We chose a bandwidth of 937.5 MHz with a spectral resolution of 0.42 km/s.  The spectral resolution is perfectly adequate for the extragalactic observation proposed here. We have selected dual polarization products, and placed four spectral windows with central frequencies separated so as to provide a small overlap at the band edges.  In all the science goals, the spectral coverage includes the water line, H2O 2_20-2_11, at 1228 GHz (which we detected serendipitously in previous IRAM observations of APM 08279+5255).
 
 Imaging requirements:
 
 The Cloverleaf quasar is a compact source, we have chosen to optimize our sensitivity by using the Early Science Compact Configuration.</prj:justificationText>
        </prj:TechnicalJustification>
