        <prj:TechnicalJustification>
            <prj:justificationText>Required sensitivity:

The rms noise of 1 mJy at 10 km/s resolution gives a SNR of ~40 on the continuum for the HATLAS J142413.9+022304 (taking a continuum flux at 1.2 mm of ~ 40 mJy), sufficient to detect a possible absorption feature, even if the line is not completely saturated. If the HF line is in emission we will get a SNR of 10-12 based upon the peak intensity of the water line (Omont et al. 2013), assumption validated from nearby observations where the HF line, when in emission, presents similar or stronger peak intensity that the water lines. 


Correlator setup:

 We chose a bandwidth of 1875 MHz with a spectral resolution of 1.2 km/s.  The spectral resolution is perfectly adequate for the extragalactic observation proposed here.  We have selected dual polarization products, and placed four spectral windows with central frequencies separated so as to provide a small overlap at the band edges. The spectral setup allows to place the HF and water line, H2O 2_20-2_11 in the upper side band (USB) and the water lines H2O 3_12-2_21 and 3_21-3_12 in the lower side band (LSB). 
 
 </prj:justificationText>
