        <prj:TechnicalJustification>
            <prj:justificationText>Required sensitivity:

The rms noise of 1 mJy at 10 km/s resolution gives a SNR of ~ 40 on the continuum for the HATLAS J114637.9-001132 (taking a continuum flux at 1.2 mm of ~ 40 mJy), sufficient to detect a possible absorption feature, even if the line is not completely saturated. If the HF line is in emission we will get a SNR of 30 based upon the peak intensity of the water line (Omont et al. 2013), assumption based on nearby observations where the HF line, when in emission, presents similar or stronger peak intensity that the water lines. 


Correlator setup:

 We chose a bandwidth of 937.5 MHz with a spectral resolution of 0.22 km/s.  The spectral resolution is perfectly adequate for the extragalactic observation proposed here. We have selected dual polarization products, and placed four spectral windows with central frequencies separated so as to provide a small overlap at the band edges.  The spectral coverage includes the water line, H2O 2_20-2_11, at 1228 GHz.
 
 </prj:justificationText>
